The paper deals with information embedding in a Gaussian host signal and its recovery, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the Witsenhausen counterexample, which is a well-known problem in distributed control (cs.SY). The use of dirty-paper coding and the optimization of rate for perfect recovery suggest that the paper may also fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) or cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper's focus on achieving optimal costs and providing bounds suggests that it may also belong to the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
